account_id.description: The ID number of your ad account, which groups your advertising activity. Your ad account includes your campaigns, ads and billing.

account_name.description: The name of your ad account, which groups your advertising activity. Your ad account includes your campaigns, ads and billing.

action_values.description: The total value of all conversions attributed to your ads.

actions.description: The total number of actions people took that are attributed to your ads. Actions may include engagement, clicks or conversions.

ad_id.description: The unique ID of the ad you're viewing in reporting.

ad_name.description: The name of the ad you're viewing in reporting.

adset_id.description: The unique ID of the ad set you're viewing in reporting. An ad set is a group of ads that share the same budget, schedule, delivery optimization and targeting.

adset_name.description: The name of the ad set you're viewing in reporting. An ad set is a group of ads that share the same budget, schedule, delivery optimization and targeting.

app_store_clicks.description: The number of clicks on links to an app store in your ads.

buying_type.description: The method by which you pay for and target ads in your campaigns: through dynamic auction bidding, fixed-price bidding, or reach and frequency buying.

call_to_action_clicks.description: The number of times people clicked the call-to-action button on your ad.

campaign_id.description: The unique ID number of the ad campaign you're viewing in reporting. Your campaign contains ad sets and ads.

campaign_name.description: The name of the ad campaign you're viewing in reporting. Your campaign contains ad sets and ads.

canvas_avg_view_percent.description: The average percentage of the Facebook Canvas that people saw. Canvas is a screen that opens on mobile after a person clicks the Canvas link in your ad. It may include a series of interactive or multimedia components, including video, images, product catalogs and more.

canvas_avg_view_time.description: The average total time, in seconds, that people spent viewing a Facebook Canvas. Canvas is a screen that opens on mobile after a person clicks the Canvas link in your ad. It may include a series of interactive or multimedia components, including video, images, product catalogs and more.

canvas_component_avg_pct_view.description: The average percentage of time spent viewing each component of a Facebook Canvas. Canvas is a screen that opens on mobile after a person clicks the Canvas link in your ad. It may include a series of interactive or multimedia components, including video, images, product catalogs and more.

clicks.description: The number of clicks on your ads.

cost_per_10_sec_video_view.description: The average cost for each 10-second video view.

cost_per_action_type.description: The average cost of a relevant action.

cost_per_estimated_ad_recallers.description: The average cost for each estimated ad recall lift. This metric is only available for assets in the Brand Awareness Objective.

cost_per_inline_link_click.description: The average cost of each inline link click.

cost_per_inline_post_engagement.description: The average cost of each inline post engagement.

cost_per_outbound_click.description: The average cost for each outbound click.

cost_per_total_action.description: The average cost of a relevant action.

cost_per_unique_action_type.description: The average cost of each unique action.

cost_per_unique_click.description: The average cost for each unique click (all).

cost_per_unique_inline_link_click.description: The average cost of each unique inline link click.

cost_per_unique_outbound_click.description: The average cost for each unique outbound click.

cpc.description: The average cost for each click (all).

cpp.description: The average cost to reach 1,000 people.

ctr.description: The percentage of times people saw your ad and performed a click (all).

date_start.description: The start date for your data. This is controlled by the date range you've selected for your reporting view.

date_stop.description: The end date for your data. This is controlled by the date range you've selected for your reporting view.

deeplink_clicks.description: The number of clicks on links to specific parts of an app.

estimated_ad_recall_rate.description: The rate at which an estimated number of additional people, when asked, would remember seeing your ads within 2 days. This metric is only available for assets in the Brand Awareness Objective.

estimated_ad_recallers.description: An estimate of the number of additional people who may remember seeing your ads, if asked, within 2 days. This metric is only available for assets in the Brand Awareness Objective.

frequency.description: The average number of times each person saw your ad.

impressions.description: The number of times your ads were viewed.

inline_link_click_ctr.description: The percentage of time people saw your ads and performed an inline link click.

inline_link_clicks.description: The number of clicks on links to select destinations or experiences, on or off Facebook-owned properties. Inline link clicks use a fixed 1-day-click attribution window.

inline_post_engagement.description: The total number of actions that people take involving your ads. Inline post engagements use a fixed 1-day-click attribution window.

mobile_app_purchase_roas.description: The total return on ad spend (ROAS) from mobile app purchases. This is based on the value that you assigned when you set up the app event.

newsfeed_avg_position.description: The average position where your ad was inserted into people's news feeds on mobile and desktop. Position 1 is the one at the top of the feed.

newsfeed_clicks.description: The total number of clicks your ad received in people's news feed, on mobile and desktop.

newsfeed_impressions.description: The total number of times your ad was inserted into people's news feeds, on mobile and desktop.

objective.description: The objective you selected for your campaign. Your objective reflects the goal you want to achieve with your advertising.

outbound_clicks.description: The number of clicks on links that take people off Facebook-owned properties.

outbound_clicks_ctr.description: The percentage of times people saw your ad and performed an outbound click.

reach.description: The number of people who saw your ads at least once. Reach is different from impressions, which may include multiple views of your ads by the same people.

relevance_score.description: A rating from 1 to 10 that estimates how well your target audience is responding to your ad. This score is shown after your ad receives more than 500 impressions. It's only visible when looking at reporting for ads and does not appear for ad sets and campaigns.

social_clicks.description: The number of clicks (all) when your ad was displayed with social information, which shows other Facebook friends who engaged with your Facebook Page or ad.

social_impressions.description: The number of times your ads were viewed when displayed with social information, which shows Facebook friends who engaged with your Facebook Page or ad.

social_reach.description: The number of people who saw your ad when displayed with social information, which shows other Facebook friends who engaged with your Facebook Page or ad.

social_spend.description: The total amount you've spent so far for your ads showed with social information. (ex: Jane Doe likes this).

spend.description: The estimated total amount of money you've spent on your campaign, ad set or ad during its schedule.

total_action_value.description: The total value of all conversions attributed to your ads.

total_actions.description: The total number of actions people took that are attributed to your ads. Actions may include engagement, clicks or conversions.

total_unique_actions.description: The number of people who took an action that was attributed to your ads.

unique_actions.description: The number of people who took an action that was attributed to your ads.

unique_clicks.description: The number of people who performed a click (all).

unique_ctr.description: The percentage of people who saw your ad and performed a unique click (all).

unique_impressions.description: The number of people who saw your ads at least once.

unique_inline_link_click_ctr.description: The percentage of times people saw your ad and performed a link click. Inline click-through rate uses a fixed 1-day-click attribution window.

unique_inline_link_clicks.description: The number of people who performed an inline link click.

unique_link_clicks_ctr.description: The percentage of people who saw your ad and performed a link click.

unique_outbound_clicks.description: The number of people who performed an outbound click.

unique_outbound_clicks_ctr.description: The percentage of people who saw your ad and performed an outbound click.

unique_social_clicks.description: The number of people who performed a click (all) on your ad when it was displayed with social information, which shows other Facebook friends who engaged with your Facebook Page or ad.

unique_social_impressions.description: The number of people the ad was served to with social context.

video_10_sec_watched_actions.description: The number of times your video was watched for an aggregate of at least 10 seconds, or for nearly its total length, whichever happened first.

video_15_sec_watched_actions.description: The number of times your video was watched for an aggregate of at least 15 seconds, or for nearly its total length, whichever happened first.

video_30_sec_watched_actions.description: The number of times your video was watched for an aggregate of at least 30 seconds, or for nearly its total length, whichever happened first.

video_avg_percent_watched_actions.description: The average percentage of your video that people watched.

video_avg_time_watched_actions.description: The average time a video was watched.

video_complete_watched_actions.description: This shows the number of total views of at least 30 seconds or to the end of your video, whichever occurs first.

video_p100_watched_actions.description: The number of times your video was watched at 100% of its length, including watches that skipped to this point.

video_p25_watched_actions.description: The number of times your video was watched at 25% of its length, including watches that skipped to this point.

video_p50_watched_actions.description: The number of times your video was watched at 50% of its length, including watches that skipped to this point.

video_p75_watched_actions.description: The number of times your video was watched at 75% of its length, including watches that skipped to this point.

video_p95_watched_actions.description: The number of times your video was watched at 95% of its length, including watches that skipped to this point.

website_clicks.description: The number of clicks on links to your website in your ads.

website_ctr.description: The percentage of times people saw your ad and performed a link click.

website_purchase_roas.description: The total return on ad spend (ROAS) from website purchases. This is based on the value of all conversions recorded by the Facebook pixel on your website and attributed to your ads.
